reviewText:
To be completely truthful I enjoyed my time spent on the singleplayer and with a small amount of time on the multiplayer the game appears to be pretty solid. Now my review is warped by me spending only £3.99 for the game while it was on sale and of course if I paid full price for the game and bought it closer to its release this review would be totally different.

Pros;
The game is action packed and the centre of the game, the combat, feels amazingly smooth. The idea of having the likes of 2 guns in hand along with the snake like tentacles ripping people into a fine paste while going rambo is alone a good reason for purchasing the game. Graphically its not all that bad and there is little to complain about the game in this sense as it isnt all that demanding. The storyline was slightly dull at the start of the game however as the game progressed I was getting more and more into it and in the end it wasnt all the bad of a story in comparison to some modern games. The gore in this game on its own needs a special mention because OH MY LORD was it beautiful with a whole variety of different executions which seem to get more and more enjoyable with each kill as all who stand in your way squirm to release themselves from the grasp of your tentacles.

Cons;
There is very little replay value here in my opinion from this game. The singleplayer isn't all that long either with a single playthrough on the hitman difficulty taking around three to three and a half hours maximum with figuring out controls etc. There is still a bug in the game with a certain section where you go into the ventilation shaft which cannot be passed without V-Sync enabled without it you just run into invisible walls. Boss fights are extremely boring consisting of the boss teleporting and standing still for 10 seconds while you rain hell on him and then teleporting again to form a dull sequence with no real challenge. The AI for the normal grunts and even some of the specials you meet during the game are to put it plainly below average and with them all looking so similar there is a strong sense of Ctrl C + Ctrl V.

Other than that the game is pretty solid however I would only recommend it for buying during a sale as you may feel disappointed with what you are paying £19.99 for. To put a number to it;
7.5/10 on sale
5/10 full price
